snippet.title: Discriminant to Find Number of Solutions
snippet.description:
Learn about the discriminant and how to use it to find the number and type of solutions in this free math video tutorial by Mario's Math Tutoring.

0:15 What is the Discriminant
0:54 How to Know the Nature of the Roots or the Type of Solutions Using the Discriminant
1:58 Example 1 x^2+5x+4=0 Find the Number & Type of Roots (2 Real Rational Roots)
2:34 Example 2 x^2-6x+1=0 (2 Real Irrational Roots)
2:59 Example 3 2x^2 + 4x + 2 =0 (1 Real Repeated Solution)
3:27 Example 4 3x^2 + 2x + 2 =0 (0 Real 2 Complex Solutions)
